  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Trans Boundary Flood Resilience in Kamala River Basin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project builds the capacity of flood affected vulnerable communities to respond to, adjust to and prepare for floods, by increasing their resilience and adaptation capacities. The project seeks three outcomes: 1. to strengthen Community Disaster Management Committees&apos; (CDMCs) capacities to cope with shocks and stressors. 2. To reduce flood risk at the community level through trans-boundary collaboration. 3. to enroll flood vulnerable households in safety net options. The project is implemented by Aasaman Nepal.</narrative>
  </description>
